0.name: Uranium Waste
0.description:
The by-product of consuming Uranium Fuel Rods in a Nuclear Power Plant.
Non-Fissile Uranium can be extracted. Handle with caution.

Caution: HIGHLY Radioactive.

1.name: Plutonium Waste
1.description:
The by-product of consuming Plutonium Fuel Rods in a Nuclear Power Plant.
Must be stored in a safe location. Handle with caution.

Caution: EXTREMELY Radioactive.

2.name: Concrete
2.description:
Used for building.
Good for stable Foundations.

3.name: Silica
3.description: Derived from Raw Quartz. Commonly used to create glass structures, in advanced refinement processes, and for alternative production of electronics.

4.name: Iron Plate
4.description:
Used for crafting.
One of the most basic parts.

5.name: Steel Beam
5.description: Primarily used when constructing slightly more advanced buildings.

6.name: Aluminum Ingot
6.description:
Smelted from Aluminum Scrap, which is refined from Alumina Solution.
Used to produce specialized aluminum-based parts.

7.name: Battery
7.description: Primarily used as fuel for Drones and vehicles.

8.name: Packaged Fuel
8.description: Fuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

9.name: Packaged Ionized Fuel
9.description: Ionized Fuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

10.name: Packaged Rocket Fuel
10.description: Rocket Fuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

11.name: Packaged Turbofuel
11.description: Turbofuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

12.name: Iodine-Infused Filter
12.description: Absorbs radioactive particles when used with the Hazmat Suit.

13.name: Compacted Coal
13.description: A much more efficient alternative to Coal. Used as fuel for vehicles and Coal-Powered Generators.

14.name: Packaged Heavy Oil Residue
14.description: Heavy Oil Residue, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles.

15.name: Petroleum Coke
15.description:
Used for crafting.
A carbon-rich material distilled from Heavy Oil Residue. 
Used as a less efficient Coal replacement.

16.name: Packaged Oil
16.description: Crude Oil, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles.

17.name: Iron Rod
17.description:
Used for crafting.
One of the most basic parts.

18.name: Wire
18.description:
Used for crafting.
One of the most basic parts.

19.name: Cable
19.description:
Used for crafting.
Primarily used to build Power Lines.

20.name: Iron Ingot
20.description: Used for crafting the most basic parts.

21.name: Reinforced Iron Plate
21.description:
Used for crafting.
A sturdier and more durable Iron Plate.

22.name: Rotor
22.description:
Used for crafting.
The moving parts of a motor.

23.name: Fuel
23.description: Can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

24.name: Rocket Fuel
24.description:
A high-impulse compressed gas fuel.
Can be used as-is to power Fuel-Powered Generators, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

25.name: Copper Sheet
25.description:
Used for crafting.
Primarily used for Pipelines due to its high corrosion resistance.

26.name: Modular Frame
26.description:
Used for crafting.
A multipurpose building block.

27.name: Screw
27.description:
Used for crafting.
One of the most basic parts.

28.name: Nitric Acid
28.description: Produced when Nitrogen Gas reacts with Water. Its high corrosiveness and oxidizing properties make it an excellent choice for refinement and fuel production processes.

29.name: Turbofuel
29.description: A more efficient alternative to Fuel. Can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles.

30.name: Empty Fluid Tank
30.description: Used to package gases and volatile liquids for transportation.

31.name: Crystal Oscillator
31.description: An electronic oscillator circuit that uses the mechanical resonance of a vibrating crystal to create an electrical signal with a precise frequency.

32.name: Motor
32.description: Creates a mechanical force that is used to move things from machines to vehicles.

33.name: Dark Matter Crystal
33.description:
Concentrated Dark Matter Residue that is isolated within a crystalline vessel. This form of containment allows for utilising Dark Matter reliably in other production processes.

Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

34.name: Ionized Fuel
34.description:
Fuel that has been ionized, allowing it to deliver incredible output.
Can be used as-is to power Fuel-Powered Generators, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles or the Jetpack.

35.name: Supercomputer
35.description: The next-gen version of a Computer.

36.name: Cooling System
36.description: Keeps advanced parts and buildings from exceeding efficient temperature levels.

37.name: Ficsite Trigon
37.description: The Ficsite Trigon, made from Ficsite Ingots, is perfectly shaped for all construction challenges. It's performance is so exceptional, it basically solved structural engineering.

38.name: Turbo Motor
38.description: A more complex and powerful version of the regular Motor.

39.name: Time Crystal
39.description: Time Crystals are Diamonds that have been reconfigured on a sub-atomic level in the Converter to retain a time-periodic self-organizing structure. This allows them to be used in the development of quantum processing and storage technologies.

40.name: Dark Matter Residue
40.description:
Produced as a by-product of Quantum Encoding processes and alternatively generated in the Converter.

Various fields of science are still debating the nature and properties of Dark Matter. Meanwhile, FICSIT has found several applications for it in space-time manipulation.

41.name: Reanimated SAM
41.description:
The active and contained form of the Strange Alien Matter.

Proper electromagnetic containment is required, as it appears to be able to manipulate the atomic bonds of any matter it comes into contact with.

42.name: Excited Photonic Matter
42.description:
Excited Photonic Matter is essential for all production processes in the Quantum Encoder.

Formed in the Converter by inducing intense photon interactions through exposure to SAM in a high-energy environment.

43.name: Diamonds
43.description:
Synthetic Diamonds produced by exposing Coal to extreme heat and pressure.

Used in the production of Time Crystals and Dark Matter Crystals.

Power Usage: 250-750 MW (500 MW average).

44.name: Alclad Aluminum Sheet
44.description: Used to make products that require high heat conduction or a high specific strength. Thin, lightweight, and highly durable.

45.name: Superposition Oscillator
45.description: An oscillator circuit that uses the mechanical resonance of a vibrating crystal to create a string vibration with a precise frequency. Often used in teleportation technology and dimensional manipulation.

46.name: Neural-Quantum Processor
46.description: The Neural-Quantum Processor utilizes a combination of neural network architecture and quantum computing techniques to achieve unprecedented performance. This technology has enabled some of FICSIT's biggest advancements in artificial intelligence and relativistic engineering.

47.name: AI Expansion Server
47.description:
Project Part #12. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
Power Usage: 1500-2500 MW (2000 MW average).

Growth is the metric by which we measure success.

48.name: Magnetic Field Generator
48.description:
Project Part #7. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

These modular generators use superconducting magnets and vast amounts of electricity to produce a powerful and easily expandable magnetic field.

49.name: SAM Fluctuator
49.description:
The SAM Fluctuator is able to regulate and direct the behaviour of Reanimated SAM through the application of electric charges with varying frequencies.
This control facilitates technologies such as matter-to-energy conversion and spatiotemporal matter manipulation.

50.name: Steel Pipe
50.description: Primarily used when constructing slightly more advanced buildings.

51.name: Fused Modular Frame
51.description: A corrosion-resistant, nitride-hardened, highly-robust-yet-lightweight modular frame.

53.name: Ficsite Ingot
53.description:
Produced by reconstructing other metals on a molecular level using Strange Alien Matter.

Synthesized by FICSIT to be the perfect construction material, and used in the most high-end processes.

54.name: Biochemical Sculptor
54.description:
Project Part #10. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

Years ahead of the competition, this top-of-the-line 3D printer is used for the production of synthetic biological resources.

55.name: Assembly Director System
55.description:
Project Part #6. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

This extremely fast and precise computing system is specifically designed to direct the Project Assembly: Assembly Phase.

56.name: Caterium Ingot
56.description: Smelted from Caterium Ore. Primarily used for advanced electronics.

57.name: Empty Canister
57.description: Used to package fluids for transportation.

58.name: Circuit Board
58.description: Advanced electronics that have a plethora of different uses.

59.name: Plastic
59.description: Versatile and easy to manufacture, this material has a wide range of uses.

60.name: Encased Industrial Beam
60.description:
Simultaneously utilizes the compressive strength of concrete and the tensile strength of steel.
Mostly used as a stable base for constructing buildings.

61.name: Rubber
61.description: A very flexible material that has a lot of friction.

62.name: Polymer Resin
62.description: A by-product of Crude Oil refinement into Fuel. Commonly used to manufacture Plastic and Rubber.

63.name: Heavy Oil Residue
63.description: A by-product of Plastic and Rubber production. Can be further refined into Fuel and Petroleum Coke.

64.name: Quartz Crystal
64.description: Derived from Raw Quartz. Used in the production of advanced radar technology and high-quality display screens.

65.name: Steel Ingot
65.description: Smelted from a combination of Iron Ore and Coal. Can be made into several parts used in building construction.

66.name: Versatile Framework
66.description: Project Part #2. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

68.name: Copper Ingot
68.description: Used for crafting the most basic parts.

69.name: Aluminum Scrap
69.description: Refined from Alumina. Can be smelted into Aluminum Ingots for industrial usage.

70.name: Aluminum Casing
70.description: A versatile container cast from Aluminum Ingots.

71.name: Alumina Solution
71.description: Dissolved Alumina, extracted from Bauxite. Can be further refined into Aluminum Scrap for Aluminum Ingot production.

72.name: Computer
72.description: A complex logic machine that is used to control advanced behavior in other machines.

74.name: Smart Plating
74.description: Project Part #1. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

75.name: High-Speed Connector
75.description: Connects multiple cables and wires in a very efficient way. Uses a standard pattern, so it has many varied applications.

76.name: Automated Wiring
76.description: Project Part #3. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

77.name: Stator
77.description:
Used for crafting.
The static parts of a motor.

78.name: AI Limiter
78.description: Controls AIs and keeps them from evolving in malicious ways. Super advanced electronics.

79.name: Quickwire
79.description: Caterium's high conductivity and resistance to corrosion make it ideal for small, advanced electronics.

80.name: Modular Engine
80.description: Project Part #4. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

81.name: Adaptive Control Unit
81.description: Project Part #5. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

82.name: Pressure Conversion Cube
82.description: Converts outgoing force into internal pressure. Required to contain unstable, high-energy matter.

83.name: Encased Plutonium Cell
83.description:
Plutonium Pellets encased in concrete.
Used to produce Plutonium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production.

Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

84.name: Plutonium Pellet
84.description:
Produced in the Particle Accelerator through conversion of Non-fissile Uranium.
Used to produce Encased Plutonium Cells for Plutonium Fuel Rods.

Power Usage: 250-750 MW (500 MW average).
Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

85.name: Non-Fissile Uranium
85.description:
The Uranium-238 isotope is non-fissile, meaning it cannot be used for nuclear fission. It can, however, be converted into fissile Plutonium in the Particle Accelerator.

Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

86.name: Sulfuric Acid
86.description: Produced by combining Sulfur and Water in a complex reaction. Primarily used in refinement processes and Battery production.

87.name: Copper Powder
87.description:
Ground-up Copper Ingots.
The high natural density of Copper, combined with the granularity of the powder, makes this part perfect for producing Nuclear Pasta in the Particle Accelerator.

90.name: Nuclear Pasta
90.description:
Project Part #9. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

Nuclear Pasta is extremely dense degenerate matter, formed when extreme pressure forces protons and electrons together into neutrons. It is theorized to exist naturally within the crust of neutron stars.

91.name: Encased Uranium Cell
91.description:
Used to produce Uranium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production. Made from Uranium Ore.

Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

92.name: Dissolved Silica
92.description:
Silica dissolved in Water, produced as part of the alternative refinement of Raw Quartz.
The Silica can be extracted from the Water to complete the refinement process.

93.name: Thermal Propulsion Rocket
93.description:
Project Part #8. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

Uses extreme heat to produce the high-pressure plasma required to get Project Assembly into motion.

94.name: Black Powder
94.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce simple explosives.

95.name: Ficsonium
95.description:
Usage and production of this material is strictly prohibited. On Earth, that is. There are no rules in space, only efficiency. 

Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).

96.name: Singularity Cell
96.description: Used to break down space and time. Required to power Portals.

97.name: Ballistic Warp Drive
97.description:
Project Part #11. Ship via the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
Power Usage: 1000-2000 MW (1500 MW average).

A large amount of force is required for the Warp Drives to activate, so sticking them to rockets was the logical next step. Additionally, results improved immensely when the observers were further removed from the Warp Drives upon activation.

98.name: Gas Filter
98.description: Filters out toxins and pollutants from the air when used with a Gas Mask.

99.name: Alien Protein
99.description:
Ground-up Alien Remains in a neat little package.
Used for medical purposes and to research alien organisms.

100.name: Blue Power Slug
100.description: A strange slug radiating an unknown weak power.

101.name: Alien DNA Capsule
101.description:
Translates organic chemicals into readable alien genetic information.
Used for researching alien organisms.

Go the extra kilometer! Knowledge is power, and power is just efficiency with fewer steps. Depositing Alien DNA Capsules in the AWESOME Sink provides FICSIT with knowledge, and pioneers with Coupons.

102.name: Mercer Sphere
102.description: A weird alien phenomenon. While the sphere appears liquid, it behaves like a solid and does not have any detectable mass. It seems to somehow interact with and have awareness of its environment.

103.name: Purple Power Slug
103.description: A strange slug radiating a powerful unknown power.

104.name: Yellow Power Slug
104.description: A strange slug radiating an unknown power.

105.name: Smokeless Powder
105.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce modern firearms.

106.name: Rebar Gun
106.description: An improvised ranged weapon for self-defense. Has to be reloaded after each use.

107.name: Rifle
107.description: A long-range, rapid-fire weapon. Specifically designed to deliver adequate performance within the designated work area.

108.name: Uranium Fuel Rod
108.description:
Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.

Caution: Produces radioactive Uranium Waste when consumed.
Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

109.name: Plutonium Fuel Rod
109.description:
Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.

Caution: Produces radioactive Plutonium Waste when consumed.
Caution: HIGHLY Radioactive.

110.name: Ficsonium Fuel Rod
110.description:
Used as fuel for Nuclear Power Plants.
The power source that put FICSIT on the map. Literally. The crater is still there.

Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

111.name: Explosive Rebar
111.description: Explodes on impact, dealing heavy damage.

112.name: Stun Rebar
112.description:
Electrocutes the target on impact, stunning it for a short time.

Stun Duration: 5 seconds

113.name: Homing Rifle Ammo
113.description:
The bullet guidance system built into this ammunition allows it to accurately hit any target within the reticle area.
Especially useful when dealing with agile threats, or for pioneers who can't be bothered to aim properly.

114.name: Cluster Nobelisk
114.description: Detonates into multiple smaller explosions. Practical for clearing out large areas of vegetation and other inconveniences.

115.name: Nobelisk
115.description: A simple explosive, useful for clearing boulders, vegetation, and other obstacles.

116.name: Gas Nobelisk
116.description: Creates a deadly gas cloud instead of a regular explosion.

117.name: Nuke Nobelisk
117.description:
Uses a nuclear fission reaction to generate a massive explosion.
WARNING: Ensure all FICSIT property is clear of the blast zone before detonation.

118.name: Pulse Nobelisk
118.description: Generates a powerful shockwave instead of a regular explosion.

119.name: Iron Rebar
119.description: Can be shot using the Rebar Gun for self-defense purposes.

120.name: Hazmat Suit
120.description:
Shields pioneers from the adverse effects of radiation. 
Consumes Iodine-Infused Filters from the pioneer's inventory when worn in radioactive areas.

121.name: Nobelisk Detonator
121.description: A remote-control device used to handle and detonate Nobelisks.

122.name: Factory Cart™
122.description:
The one and only FICSIT Factory Cart™.
Now with special FICSIT-Foundation-only Grip Wheels, for an even smoother and faster factory floor experience!

123.name: Golden Factory Cart™
123.description:
The one and only Golden FICSIT Factory Cart™

You have now officially ascended. 
Go forth now, Master of Spaghetti, God of the Factory, Sinker of Cups, Employee of the Planet... travel in STYLE!

124.name: Portable Miner
124.description:
Automatically extracts a resource when placed on a resource node.
Note: Has limited storage space.

125.name: Xeno-Zapper
125.description: A standard issue self-defense electroshock melee weapon.

126.name: Object Scanner
126.description: Scans the area for a selected item. Beeps at a rate proportional to proximity and direction.

127.name: Hoverpack
127.description:
Power Consumption: 100 MW

Allows pioneers to move vertically and hover in mid-air to improve building efficiency and factory traversal. Wirelessly connects to nearby power connections, such as Power Poles and Buildings, for power consumption.

Slow-Fall: Hold {PlayerMovement_Jump} after losing connection mid-air.
Disable Hoverpack: Double tap {PlayerMovement_Crouch} while hovering.

128.name: Jetpack
128.description:
Allows pioneers to travel through the air with increased control.

Fuel is automatically consumed from the pioneer's inventory to refill the Jetpack while on the ground.
Different fuel types can be used and provide different levels of Jetpack efficiency. The preferred fuel type will be used if available, and can be set in the equipment inventory.

129.name: Xeno-Basher
129.description: A heavy self-defense electroshock melee weapon.

130.name: Chainsaw
130.description:
Clears an area of flora that is too difficult to remove by hand.

Fuel: Biofuel

131.name: Blade Runners
131.description:
An exoskeleton for the lower legs that assists movement, allowing pioneers to sprint faster and jump higher.
Also dampens the impact of landing.

132.name: Zipline
132.description:
Provides faster traversal of factories by allowing pioneers to zip along Power lines.
Activate the Zipline and aim at a nearby Power Line to connect to it.

133.name: Gas Mask
133.description:
Allows pioneers to breathe normally in toxic gas-filled areas.
Consumes Gas Filters from the pioneer's inventory when in use.

134.name: Shatter Rebar
134.description: Fractures when shot, launching deadly debris with wide spread but limited range.

135.name: Turbo Rifle Ammo
135.description: Lightweight, compact, and volatile. These rounds provide extreme capacity and rate of fire at the cost of accuracy.

136.name: Rifle Ammo
136.description: Standard issue Rifle ammunition, useful for establishing dominance.

137.name: Iron Ore
137.description:
Used for crafting.
The most essential basic resource.

138.name: Coal
138.description: Mainly used as fuel for vehicles & Coal-Powered Generators, or in Steel production.

140.name: Nitrogen Gas
140.description: Has a variety of uses, including metallurgy, cooling, and Nitric Acid production. On MASSAGE-2 (AB)b, it can be extracted from underground gas wells.

141.name: Sulfur
141.description: Primarily used to produce Black Powder.

142.name: SAM
142.description: Strange Alien Matter, commonly referred to as SAM, doesn't seem to follow the known laws of physics. It whispers of new possibilities.

143.name: Bauxite
143.description: Used to produce Alumina, which can be further refined into the Aluminum Scrap required to produce Aluminum Ingots.

144.name: Caterium Ore
144.description: Smelted into Caterium Ingots, which are primarily used for advanced electronics.

145.name: Copper Ore
145.description:
Used for crafting.
A basic resource primarily used for electricity.

146.name: Raw Quartz
146.description: Can be processed into Quartz Crystals and Silica, which both offer a variety of applications.

147.name: Limestone
147.description:
Used for crafting.
A basic resource primarily used for stable Foundations.

148.name: Uranium
148.description:
A radioactive element. 
Used to produce Encased Uranium Cells for Uranium Fuel Rods.

Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

149.name: Crude Oil
149.description: Refined into all kinds of Oil-based resources, like Fuel and Plastic.

150.name: Medicinal Inhaler
150.description:
Fully restores health when used.

The FICSIT Medicinal Inhaler can be produced from a variety of different ingredients.

151.name: Solid Biofuel
151.description: The most energy-efficient form of solid Biomass. Can be used as fuel for the Chainsaw.

152.name: Packaged Liquid Biofuel
152.description: Liquid Biofuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for vehicles and the Jetpack.

153.name: Biomass
153.description:
Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can use it for power.
Biomass is much more energy-efficient than raw biological matter.

154.name: Leaves
154.description:
Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can use Leaves for power.

155.name: Mycelia
155.description:
Used for crafting.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can also use Mycelia for power.

156.name: Wood
156.description:
Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can use Wood for power.

157.name: Liquid Biofuel
157.description: Liquid Biofuel can be used as-is to generate power, or packaged to be used as fuel for vehicles.

158.name: Packaged Alumina Solution
158.description: Alumina Solution, packaged for alternative transport.

159.name: Packaged Nitrogen Gas
159.description: Nitrogen Gas, packaged for alternative transport.

160.name: Packaged Nitric Acid
160.description: Nitric Acid, packaged for alternative transport.

161.name: Packaged Sulfuric Acid
161.description: Sulfuric Acid, packaged for alternative transport.

162.name: Fabric
162.description:
Used to craft equipment.
Flexible but durable fabric.

163.name: Hog Remains
163.description:
The carapace of an alien Hog creature.
Used for MAM research.

164.name: Spitter Remains
164.description:
The remains of a plasma-spitting alien creature.
Used for MAM research.

165.name: Stinger Remains
165.description:
The remains of whatever that creepy thing was.
Used for MAM research.

166.name: Hatcher Remains
166.description:
The shell-like remains of an alien... thing.
Used for MAM research.

167.name: Power Shard
167.description:
Power Slug mucus compressed into a solid crystal-like shard. 
It radiates a strange power.

168.name: Somersloop
168.description: An odd alien object with a mind-bending, yet somehow familiar shape. It emits an unsettling energy.

169.name: Paleberry
169.description:
Consumable

Eat to restore 1 health segment.

170.name: Beryl Nut
170.description:
Consumable

Eat to restore half a health segment.

171.name: Bacon Agaric
171.description:
Consumable

Eat to restore 2 health segments.

172.name: Parachute
172.description: Slows down your fall when activated in mid-air.
